[2 bladen] Resurrection: [blad 1, recto] I. a) Drawing: Rotterdam; b) Goppelsroeder-Sarasin painting; c) Painting in Freiburg i. Br. Stadt Sammlungen, (old) Phot.u. Verlag G. Röbeke Freiburg i. Br. N° 435 (Christi Auferstehung: Brueghel [...]; Reversed composition II. a) Engraving; b) Liverpool painting; c) L. van Hooff painting; d) De Ruiter painting. In each version of II there is a different landscape in the background. In II d) the women look least like Bruegel; [blad 1, verso] [...]; [blad 2, recto] Resurrection Bastelaer II 4. There is a second state, not mentioned by Bastelaer), inscribed: BRVEGEL INVEN GALLE EXCVDEBAT. (repr. in Dvorak, Kunstgesch. als Geistegesch., pl. 38). The print has the same kind of frame as the Bailleur, Bast. 278.[scan]
